Game Platform Intsallation Manual

1) required python libraries:

wx2.8, pymouse

2) required ubuntu packages:

xautomation
libxss-dev
xbindkeys

3) configuring xbindkeys

Enter the following command in the terminal:

xbindkeys --defaults > $HOME/.xbindkeysrc

A hidden configuration file called '.xbindkeysrc' will appear in your HOME directory.

Add the following two lines to the file.

"xte 'keydown space'"
  b:1

"xte 'keyup space'"
  b:1 + release

Finally add a 'killall xbindkeys' command to your startup applications.

4) compiling idle.c

Call the terminal command:

gcc -o idle idle.c -lXss

in the idle.c directory.


Sources: 

http://coderrr.wordpress.com/2008/04/20/getting-idle-time-in-unix/
